Get Data

getSymbols

An unified interface to obtain data from multiple sources.

library(quantmod)
apple <- getSymbols(Symbols = "AAPL", src = "yahoo", auto.assign = FALSE)
head(apple)
           AAPL.Open AAPL.High AAPL.Low AAPL.Close AAPL.Volume AAPL.Adjusted
2007-01-03     86.29     86.58    81.90      83.80   309579900      10.85709
2007-01-04     84.05     85.95    83.82      85.66   211815100      11.09807
2007-01-05     85.77     86.20    84.40      85.05   208685400      11.01904
2007-01-08     85.96     86.53    85.28      85.47   199276700      11.07345
2007-01-09     86.45     92.98    85.15      92.57   837324600      11.99333
2007-01-10     94.75     97.80    93.45      97.00   738220000      12.56728

The objects can be auto assigned to the environment.

getSymbols("SPY")

[1] "SPY"

Quandl

Another option is to download the data from the Internet via the Quandl API.

gdp <- Quandl("FRED/GDP", type = "xts")
autoplot.zoo(gdp)
